**Abstract:**
Detailed research notes on the 1980 critical edition of William d'Auxerre's *Summa Aurea* (c.1220), edited by Jean Ribaillier. Notes on manuscript history, structure of the work, long and short recensions, citations (Augustine, Abelard, Anselm, Aristotle, Boethius, Dionysius, Lombard). Part of Xavier's research on 13th-century theology and the Aristotelian revolution in medieval thought.

